#### 

§ 30. THE SIX ORGANS OF SENSE.

<span class="small">Translated from the Samyutta-Nikâya
(xii.2<sup>11</sup>).</span>

   And what, O priests, are the six organs of sense?

   Eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind--these, O priests, are called
the six organs of sense.

